Pseudocode for TipCalculator

Variables, constants

    - tax: Double, use 2.5%
    - recommendedTip: Double, use 17.5%

    - itemCost: Double, user inputted item cost
    - itemsArray: array containing all the items' cost

    - totalCost: Double, cost of all items pretax
    - totalTax: Double, tax of 2.5% on totalCost
    - tip: Double, 17.5% of the totalCost

    - total: Double, add totalCost, totalTax, and tip

    - two Digits: DecimalFormatter, convert double to string with two decimals

Process

    - Prompt user to enter an item cost
    - validate the input
    - continue doing this until user presses 0
    - calculate totalCost (add items in array)
    - calculate totalTax = tax * totalCost
    - calculate tip = recommendedTip * totalCost
    - calculate total, add totalCost, totalTax, and tip

    - ask user if they want to try a different tip percentage
    - display new results

Function

    getCost()
        - prompt user to enter a cost
        - if itemCost < 0, ask again
        - continue until item is non-negative
        - return itemCost

